snippet.textDisplay:
I bought the airpods, thinking they were overpriced, but there’s legitimate value in being able to listen to your phone wirelessly, easily switching to your laptop or switch (switch needs an adapter) Listening to directions while your phone is hooked up to a powerbank in a backpack while traveling, double tapping the left or right ear to skip or repeat songs is great while on the bike, and it even works through multiple layers of clothing over your head.

The convenience of carrying 24 hours of charge time with you makes it so much more of a useable everyday product. I love them!
